    <title ob="x" eb="" sr="">Long press on a task does not show the task menu.</title>
    <desc>
        <parg ob="" eb="" sr="" id="1">
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="1.1">Describe the bug</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="1.2">I wanted to edit the times on my current task.</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="1.3">Usually I long press and get a meny where I can select "show times" and from there on select "edit times".</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="1.4">However, long-press now results in a pop-up called "activities menu" that is empty,</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="1.5">Currently I can't find another way to edit the times.</st>
        </parg>
        <parg ob="" eb="" sr="" id="2">
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="2.1">To Reproduce</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="2.2">Steps to reproduce the behavior:</st>
        </parg>
        <parg ob="" eb="" sr="" id="3">
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="x" id="3.1">1. Create a task.</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="x" id="3.2">2. Start the timer on the task.</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="x" id="3.3">3. Long-press the task.</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="3.4">Expected behavior</st>
            <st ob="" eb="x" sr="" id="3.5">The menu that allows changing task details should appear.</st>
        </parg>
        <parg ob="" eb="" sr="" id="4">
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="4.1">Actual behavior</st>
            <st ob="x" eb="" sr="" id="4.2">Empty meny shown called "activities menu".</st>
        </parg>
